vallibrary.measures.nullm
Class NullMeasureHierarchicalA

java.lang.Object
  vallibrary.measures.Measure
      vallibrary.measures.NullMeasure
          vallibrary.measures.nullm.NullMeasureHierarchicalA

public class NullMeasureHierarchicalA
extends NullMeasure

The Null_Measure_Hierarchical_Precision class provides an object that encapsulates methods and all the informations for computing Null Measure and relative assessment by computing average adjusted rand index. This class has to be used only for hierarchical clustering methods and allows to reduce the computing time nedeed to obtain hierarchical clustering solutions (Average Linkage, Complete Linkage and Single Linkage methods). This class takes in input a Data Matrix and an Input_Measure object. Values of the measure are equal to NaN and are returned in a Measure_Vector object. The effect of computing such a measure is basically to produce Adjusted rand value with algorithm A and Benchmark dataset D

Version:
1.0
Author:
